 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search R&D Tax Accountant (remote) Boast Capital Austin, TX Remote Job details Salary $85,000 - $100,000 a year Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Each year the US and Canadian governments give out billions of dollars in R&D tax credits and innovation incentives to fund businesses, but the application process is cumbersome, time-consuming, and receiving the money can take 12+ months. 
Boast.AI is building the future of tax credit recovery with artificial intelligence so companies can get more money, faster for less time and risk. 
Boast’s mission is to help innovative companies become successful. While we serve that mission through our product, we’ve also built a non-profit community of 90k+ technology professionals called Traction to take that mission further, bringing leaders from the fastest growing companies like Google, Shopify, Twilio, Slack, LinkedIn, Zoho, GitHub, Cloudflare, and many more to share advice via weekly webinars, regular meetups, and an annual conference. 
We've secured $123M USD in funding and have been featured in TechCrunch, VentureBeat, Fox Business, Forbes, and other publications as a force in the space. 
Come join our mission to drive innovation and entrepreneurship through technology! 
As a R&D Tax Accountant at Boast.ai you are the primary expert on all R&D tax related issues for Boast’s portfolio of companies that are all building highly innovative technology. Your responsibilities will include and are not limited to: 
What you'll do:
 Directly support internal R&D tax team and customers with all tax questions Assist R&D tax team with all aspects of financial preparation for preparing R&D tax claims Prepare and review federal and state return filings for LLCs, C-Corps, and S-Corps Prepare responses to Initial Document Requests from IRS to defend customers R&D tax claims Represent customers with IRS, State or other audits Support R&D tax team and ensure that quarterly payroll filings include R&D tax credits Develop and maintain strong relationships with customers through ongoing communication and exceptional service 
What you'll need: Must have a university Accounting Degree with US CPA accreditation5+ years experience in accounting and tax, including direct experience at handling IRS audits High level of professionalism with outstanding ability to work effectively and efficiently with external client personnel at all levels of management Excellent time management skills as well as the ability to work independently and handle multiple client projects simultaneously Superior written and verbal communication skills, and the ability to capture an audience during a presentation Experience with office productivity tools Energy, passion, humor, compassion and enthusiasm Big 4 experience a plus Masters degree a plus Previous experience with R&D tax and/or other technology grants a plus 
Why you'll love working here: Competitive comp package Salary range: 85000 to 100000 USD Remote first and flexible work culture Open and transparent management structure – collaboration is how we make decisions happen Career growth within this role, including leadership and product innovation opportunities Continuous learning opportunities to promote personal and professional growth 
- Generous vacation time, encouraging you to take the time you need - we trust you to strike the right work/life balance Annual company retreats in exotic destinations and periodic team-building outings Access to our community events and conferences 
